OL,3,CWhy is Staffordshire's water supply
OL,4,Cunder pressure?
OL,6,FStaffordshire's water supply is under
OL,7,Fincreasing pressure as the recent
OL,8,Fspell of hot weather sends demand
OL,9,Fsoaring across the county.
OL,11,FWhile reservoirs still have plenty of
OL,12,Fwater, people are using it faster than
OL,13,Fit can be treated and supplied to
OL,14,Fhomes and businesses.
OL,16,FThe water supplier Severn Trent has
OL,17,Fdeclared what they call a "drought
OL,18,Ftrigger" which they say means water is
OL,19,Fbeing used faster than it can
OL,20,Fnaturally be replaced.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
